I'm assuming that you are talking about the Domino designer tool. 
According to the documentation, one can either use the tool to generate html code, or one can insert pre-written code. 
For the latter instance, the TH tag is supported. 
If the issue is pass through HTML, thats a horse of a different color. 
Many tools let the developer/designer get away with not writing alt tags, etc. Front Page is such a tool, and given that the Microsoft platform is the most proliferate at the government level, it seems a more problematic issue. 
