Yes I was looking at being able to generate the 'th' element without reverting to hand coding html. 
I think that the biggest leverage with Lotus is a focus on the 508 legislation / WAI checkpoint 'Row and column headers shall be identified for data tables' I don't think it would be too big a stretch for them to build it into Domino Designer. 
They have been very good at considering accessibility of the Lotus Notes client. 
Interestingly enough when Domino renders a view to the web it does so as a table, with 'th' elements for the column titles. 
Thus it is possible to create a table that satisfies the letter of the above law, but how the resulting 'table' would perform under a screen reader I don't know. 
